title: Facebook Is Not Making A Key Public Relations Point
text: Facebook and other Silicon Valley companies are failing to highlight how they boost economies and help SMBs grow.  In contrast, Jack Ma of Alibaba "gets it," notes Sir Martin Sorrell.

title: Most Americans would try banking with a tech giant: Bain survey
text: Sixty-two percent of U.S. respondents said they would buy a financial product from an established tech company, according to a recent report from Bain. CNBC's Kate Rooney reports on "Closing Bell."

title: Nasdaq Leads Rally: Facebook, Mastercard Break Out; Software Revives
text: Stocks shrug off retail woes: Facebook, Mastercard clear buy points; software revives.

title: Columbia Law School's Katharina Pistor on Facebook's Libra
text: Columbia Law School Professor of Comparative Law, Katharina Pistor discusses regulation for Facebook's Libra.  She speaks with Romaine Bostic, Joe Weisenthal and Caroline Hyde on "What'd You Miss?"

title: 3 Underloved Tech Stocks Making a Comeback
text: These three tech stocks fell out of favor, but buyers are returning and that makes them top stocks to buy now. Here are the key levels to watch.

title: Majority of Americans would try banking with big tech, Bain report says
text: Americans are increasingly comfortable ditching traditional banks for big tech, according to a new Bain report.

title: Dow Tops 28,000: 7 Hot Stocks Behind the Rally
text: The dual tailwinds of renewed trade optimism and stronger-than-expected corporate earnings drove the rally. The bullishness was further fueled by rate cuts by the Federal Reserve.
